shared_text:
Gia Allen‎Imagine Prep at Surprise
September 9 at 5:19 PM ·

Hi All!

I’m the foreign exchange manager for Education, Travel & Culture. We are so excited to have 7 exchange students attending Imagine Prep this year! We have a host family that opened their home to Maximilien & Kerman as a welcome family. They are able to host until October 1st.

I’m posting here to see if any families would be interested in hosting one or both of these students? The host family must be able to provide 3 meals/day & a room. They can share a room with someone of the same gender & similar age.

Our students have their own spending money & health insurance. If you want more information please feel free to call/text/email me!

623-693-1495
Gallen@edutrav.org

Thank you!

post_text:
Today's Senior Spotlight shines on Gabriel Navarro!

Gabriel plans to attend Northern Arizona University and obtain a degree in Biology and to work towards innovating the field. he also wants to work in Environmental Science/Marine Biology to help further research clean energy and waste cleanup in our oceans.

Gabriel did sports such as Cross Country & Track & Field during his freshman year. Then in 10th grade, he joined the National Honors Society and was a part of Crew Me 2 We. Outside of school life, he also loves to do photography, music, and baking.

A staff member that has really impacted Gabriel is Ms. Franco, her class and her as a person taught him so much about life and how to become a better person, he doesn't know who he'd be now if he didn't take that class.

#SeniorSpotlight #Classof2021 #RepthePrep #SurprisePrep #Stormtastic

post_text: You aren't alone when you feel stressed, frustrated, or even a bit joyful when you don't have to put your polo and belt on each morning. Virtual learning is and will continue to be a learning curve for educators, students, and parents. Know that we are here to support. While it is normal to have feelings of sadness or loneliness because of our circumstances, it is not normal for those feelings to be prolonged or so severe that they interrupt your ability to participate in school or work. If you are struggling and need a safe space to talk, my virtual door is always open. Please contact me at amy.boven@sp.imagineprep.com or 623-344-1779 to set up an appointment. http://edne.tw/n653136

post_text:
Please welcome one of our newest staff members, Mrs. Chona Pangilinan-Ronolo.
Mrs. Chona Pangilinan-Ronolo is an educator committed to collaborative learning that engages students, staff, families, and the community. Her goal is to inform, inspire and ignite the young minds as she explores the realm of science with high school students. Mrs. Ronolo graduated from Batangas State University in the Philippines with a bachelor’s degree in Secondary Education and master’s degree in Science Teaching. She served as the STEM coach and the Senior High School Science Department Team Lead and Research Coordinator in public schools in the Philippines. She has presented at both national and international science research conferences and won several awards in scientific research. She passionately believes that success in education is about building relationships.
#SurprisePrep #ImaginePrep #ImagineTogether #Stormtastic #NewStormStaff

Chris McComb, Principal

post_text:
Ever wonder where the idea for Rocky Road ice cream came from?
Sometime during the late 1920s, William Dreyer used inspiration from his partner Joseph Edy’s chocolate candy to make rocky road ice cream. Dryer did something he was probably told a hundred times not to do. He used his wife’s sewing scissors to chop up marshmallows and walnuts and added them to chocolate ice cream. Of course, it tasted good, so he was probably forgiven for using her good sewing shears for anything but fabric!
#RockyRoadDay #SurprisePrep #Stormnation #Stormtastic #ImagineTogether

post_text:
Today is Memorial Day, a day that where we honor the men and women who had died while serving in the military.
Originally, Memorial Day was known as Decoration Day, meant to honor the Union and the Confederate soldiers who died during the American Civil War and it was celebrated on May 30th. By the 1900's, it became a day to celebrate all American soldiers who died while serving in the military. It wasn't until 1967 that it was legally renamed Memorial Day and in 1971 a law was in place to make Memorial Day the last Monday in the month of May.
#MemorialDay #SurprisePrep #RepthePrep #StormNation #Stormtastic #ImagineTogether

post_text:
Cap & Gown Pickup Information:

Students with a last name that begins with letters A through K are scheduled to pick up their Cap and Gown, tomorrow (May 14th) between 10am and noon.
Students with a last name that begins with the letters L through Z are scheduled to pick up their Cap and Gown on Friday between 10am and noon (please note, that L through Z are not available for pick up tomorrow).

Upon arriving at the school, please line up on the appropriate tape marks located on the sidewalk in front of the school. Staff will assist in the distribution of regalia just outside the front office doors.

We highly encourage visitors to wear masks and recommend adults over the age of 65, or people with other health impairments, do not attend.

#Classof2020 @Seniors #capsandgown #itsgettingreal #graduation #RepthePrep #SurprisePrep #Stormtastic #ImagineTogether

shared_text:
Imagine Prep Surprise Honor Societies
April 14 at 9:50 PM ·

***Ear Savers Update***

I am overwhelmed by the response we have received from our community in regards to the ear savers we began printing due to the plea for help from the huge-hearted Youngs family.

Regrettably, I must announce that we can no longer take requests for ear savers at this time. The amount of requests that we have currently received is substantial and in order to keep from burning our personal 3D printer up we have found the need to manage expectations. The requests that have currently been confirmed by me will be filled as soon as physically possible.

Special thanks to Mr. Kevin Lancaster, IPS Science teacher, for his support with his own personal 3D printer and Principal Chris McComb for allowing the use of the Imagine Prep printer.

I understand & empathize that the need for ear savers is great. I encourage others with access to 3D printers to help in the efforts to save our essential workers from pain. I will share the public domain file via email with anyone who asks.

Thank you again!

Sincerely,
Mrs. Gia Lowell

shared_text:
Imagine Prep Surprise Honor Societies
April 7 at 11:44 PM ·

Look what’s going out to nurses in Colorado & local Banner hospitals!

Mrs. Youngs made me aware of the need for 3D printed ear savers & shared a pattern. My husband got to work & printed 58 of them in 2 days. Our very own Ryley Youngs packaged them & sent them out on our behalf.

If you have access to a 3D printer & would like to help out let me know. Front line staff need all the help we can give!

Also, let me know if you have any ideas of how else we can help.

We may have to keep our distance but no one can limit our hearts!

post_text:
Updates:
* IPS will be providing FREE breakfast AND lunch to ANY child 18 years old and younger beginning tomorrow, March 17th. Child must be present, but does not have to be a student at IPS. We will have staff outside distributing bagged meals right to your car.

* In the coming days, we will be posting to our website enrichment and exploratory activities for students and parents to consider at home. We will continue to add and update our academic recommendations for the duration of our closure.

* We are waiting on specific guidance from the Arizona Department of Education in regards to making up for lost academic time as well as guidance regarding state testing that was expected to begin in a few short weeks.

* At this time, ALL school sanctioned events and activities are postponed indefinitely (sports, clubs, field trips, etc.). We will re-evaluate events and activities after April 1st, or as recommended by local and state health officials.

post_text:
Imagine Prep Surprise will be providing Free Breakfast & Lunch for pick up starting March 17, 2020 until further notice. ALL students, 18 years and younger are welcome to partake in the program. These meals are provided through the federal National Student Lunch Program (NSLP) at no cost. Each bag/box will include one breakfast and one lunch meal per student. The student must be present to receive the meals. The meals may be picked up Monday through Friday between 9 am and 12:30 pm. You do not have to exit your car!
#reptheprep #SurprisePrep #Stormtastic #Covid_19 #coronavirus #grabandgo #grabandgomeals #pleaseshare

post_text: Update for Arizona schools on COVID-19 from Governor Doug Ducey and Superintendent of Public Instruction Kathy Hoffman.
shared_text:
Governor Doug Ducey is with Superintendent Kathy Hoffman and Arizona Department of Education.
March 15 at 5:14 PM ·

We’re joining together to keep Arizona’s kids, families, and school communities safe and healthy. Arizona is united, and we’ll get through this. Superintendent Kathy Hoffman

This decision is not made lightly, but it is the right thing to do to bring certainty and consistency to all Arizona schools. With schools closing, we are working together to provide assistance during this time and lessen the impact on all Arizona families.

It’s important for families & parents to know that while this will address operational issues, closing schools will not stop the spread of #COVID19. It is the recommendation of public health officials that kids who are not at school remain at home to the greatest extent possible.

For more information on ways to stay safe and healthy, visit http://azhealth.gov.

Read our full letter here: https://azgovernor.gov/governor/blog/2020/03/open-letter-arizona-families-educators-school-leaders-and-education-community

This decision is not made lightly, but it is the right thing to do to bring certainty and consistency to all Arizona schools. With schools closing, we are working together to provide assistance during this time and lessen the impact on all Arizona families.

It’s important for families & parents to know that while this will address operational issues, closing schools will not stop the spread of #COVID19. It is the recommendation of public health officials that kids who are not at school remain at home to the greatest extent possible.

For more information on ways to stay safe and healthy, visit http://azhealth.gov.

shared_text:
Imagine Prep Surprise PTO
February 25 at 10:30 AM ·

We are doing something crazy...Raise Craze Crazy. In order to help meet our fundraising goal to build our school amphitheater, we are doing a special 4-DAY ONLY Raffle Ticket donation to win Disneyland Family 4-pack Hopper Tickets. Ticket donations are $25 each and you can get multiple tickets. Anyone can win so please share this post. Donations made through this General Donation Link will enter the donor in the drawing. https://my.raisecraze.com/give/a5k71av/
Donations made through your student's raise craze account will enter your student in the drawing. Donations must be received Tuesday 2/25 - Friday 2/28 midnight. Drawing will be held on Monday and the winner announced on FB. Disneyland hopper tickets value is $1,000. They can be used anytime in the next 2 years with no blackout dates. Good luck and thanks for participating!

shared_text:
Imagine Prep Surprise PTO
February 21 at 2:04 PM ·

Attention Parents & Students. We need your help! We are in the final days of our big school fundraiser, called Raise Craze. Our goal is to raise $20K to build an outdoor amphitheater that will provide much needed usable space for students and teachers. So far 184 students & teachers have raised $5,255. Great job! We need the remaining 500+ students to donate at least $30. If every family would help, we could do this!
You can make a general donation here: https://my.raisecraze.com/give/a5k71av/ or register your student here: https://my.raisecraze.com/A5K71AV/
All donations are tax-deductible. Thank you!

We are halfway through our Raise Craze Fundraiser to help us build an outdoor amphitheater for students and teachers to enjoy. Thank you to the 164 students and teachers that have registered. We're asking ALL 800+ students & teachers to register so that we can reach our goal of $20,000. We have currently raised $2,730 and completed 85 Acts of Kindness. If everyone registered and raised only $25, we could easily meet our goal. Let's get rid of those rocks and create a great usable space for everyone.

This Weekend's Challenge - every student & teacher that raises $50 or more by this Sunday will be entered into a raffle for AMC Movie Passes. We can do this Storm Nation, so register today!
#RaiseCraze #RepthePrep #SurprisePrep #Stormtastic
